title: The Way of Perfection
creator: Santa Teresa de Jesus (Avila)
description: LibriVox recording of The Way of Perfection, by Santa Teresa de Jesus (Teresa of Ávila). Read by Ann Boulais. El Camino de Perfección (trans.: The Way of Perfection) is a method for making progress in the contemplative life written by St. Teresa of Ávila for the sisters of her reformed convent of the Carmelite Order (Discalced). St. Teresa was a major figure of the Catholic Reformation in 16th Century Spain. (Introduction by Wikipedia) For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
